      • GenericEvent

        public GenericEvent(java.util.UUID identifier,
                    LatLon location,
                    boolean active,
                    java.time.LocalDateTime publicationTime,
                    java.time.LocalDateTime lastEditTime,
                    java.lang.String description,
                    java.util.Set<Jam> jams,
                    EventType eventType,
                    EventPublisher source,
                    java.util.Set<TransportationType> relevantForTransportationTypes)
             throws ValidationException
        create a new generic event. This can be any kind of incident related to traffic. ex. Road obstructions, slippery roads ...
        Parameters:
        identifier - The UUID of the event.
        location - The coordinates of the location where this event is happening.
        active - Whether this event is still taking place or not.
        publicationTime - The time of publication of this event.
        lastEditTime - The last time this event was updated.
        description - A description of the event. Usually this is some extra information about the event.
        jams - All the jams that are connected to this event. An event may have no jams at all.
        eventType - The EventType of this event. ex. CONSTRUCTION.
        source - The source from where this event was obtained. ex. WAZE.
        relevantForTransportationTypes - All transportationTypes for which this event is relevant.
        Throws:
        ValidationException
